{
  "uuid": "d03242f71cfb85d22d88275aa868e010",
  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Finance & Admin Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>1. Financial Management & Governance </strong></p><ul><li><p>Lead full-set accounts, monthly closing, management reporting and annual financial statements. </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Ensure compliance with SFRS, MSF, IRAS, charity regulations, and internal finance policies. </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Liaise with auditors and accountants to ensure timely audits and clean outcomes. </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Serve as secretariat to the Finance and Audit Sub-Committees. </p></li></ul><p><strong>2. Budgeting & Financial Planning </strong></p><ul><li><p>Lead annual budgeting and periodic re-forecasting with management. </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Monitor budgets, funding utilization and cashflow. </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Provide financial analysis on cost control, sustainability and scenarios. </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Support grant budgeting and utilization tracking. </p></li></ul><p><strong>3. Strategic Financial Stewardship & Capital Planning </strong></p><ul><li><p>Develop multi-year operating and capital financial plans (5–10 years). </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Manage reserves and liquidity strategy. </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Drive revenue diversification and sustainability. </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Provide forward-looking financial insights and dashboards to Management and Board. </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Oversee financial governance for capital projects (budgets, funding milestones, cashflow, risks). </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Ensure alignment with the Singapore Code of Governance for Charities. </p></li></ul><p>Monthly reporting to focus on: </p><ul><li><p>Liquidity and reserves </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Operating performance vs budget </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Capital / rebuild funding and cost control </p></li></ul><p><strong>4. Operations (Hands-on) </strong></p><ul><li><p>Oversee AP/AR, donations, fixed assets, petty cash, bank reconciliations and payroll journals. </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Ensure proper documentation and internal controls. </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Guide and review the Finance Executive; provide operational support during peak periods and audits. </p></li></ul><p><strong>5. Systems, Process & Compliance </strong></p><ul><li><p>Review and update finance SOPs. </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Improve accounting systems and digital workflows. </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Ensure PDPA compliance and strengthen internal controls and risk management. </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Good project management skills </p></li></ul><p><strong>6. Leadership & Stakeholder Management </strong></p><ul><li><p>Coach and develop the Finance Executive. </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Partner service heads to support operations and programmes. </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Work closely with the Executive Director, Finance Sub-Committee and Board. </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Able to think strategically on how to use financial information to track, plan and forecast income and expenses and also on being a business partner to the other departments. </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Good social skills </p></li></ul><p><u><strong>Requirements </strong></u></p><ul><li><p>Degree in Accounting / Finance or equivalent professional qualification (ACCA, CPA, CA, etc.). </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Minimum 5–6 years of relevant accounting / finance experience. </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Strong knowledge of: </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Full-set accounts </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Audit processes </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Singapore regulatory environment (IRAS, MSF, charities). </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Comfortable working in a lean team and being hands-on. </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>High integrity, strong attention to detail and ability to manage deadlines independently. </p></li></ul>",
